    "attributes": {
        "action": "Require schools to operate a 4 day week",
        "additional_details": "Students with busy schedules can quickly become overwhelmed because they are left with no free time to relax. Stress can cause many serious mental health problems such as: depression, anxiety, and personal disorders. Being surrounded in an environment where students are being put on pressure is normal makes students a vulnerable target to such mental health problems.",
        "background": "I believe two days is not enough time as a break mentally. Students could use three-days spending time with family since it could improve mental health, help children perform better academically, and lower risk of behavioural problems.",
